Villarreal coach Unai Emery believes that external commitments sometimes force football stars to lose their focus on the sport. Asked about whether it is difficult to coach a team with elite players such as Kylian Mbappe and Neymar, the former Paris Saint-Germain coach explained that football stars could be surrounded by several distractions that could affect their productivity.   West Ham gets tough Sevilla draw for last 16     OLD ENEMIES: Tuchel, Klopp in titanic Carabao Cup battle     Haaland’s future to be decided soon   “It’s hard to get it right because you have to work on football as well,” Emery told TNT Sports.”For what it means to have those footballers who have so many things around them, you have to try to focus a lot on football. “The players do it, but someone may have many other external obligations that sometimes moves them away from football. “But it is a pleasure to work with players of that level.”